1. <constraint name>.constraint_mode(0) -> disable constraint
2. <constraint name>.constraint_mode(1) -> enable constraint
3. constraint with same name in the derived class overrides the constraint in the base class
4. The initial specifier, preceded by a colon, when applied to constraints, specifies that the constraint shall not be an override.
5. The final specifier, when applied to constraints, specifies that no further replacements of the constraint shall be allowed.
6. function void object.rand_mode(bit on_off) 
7. function int object.random_variable.rand_mode()
8. function void object.constraint_mode(bit on_off)
9. function int object.constraint_block.constraint_mode()
